The original manuscript for Don McLean's iconic hit 'American Pie' is set to fetch $1.5million when it is sold at auction later this year.

The 16-page handwritten and typed draft, which includes notes and deletions is to go under the hammer at Christie's in New York in April.

The song was released in 1971 and was named Song of the Century by the Recording Industry Association of America and the National Endowment for the Arts.

