Mr McLean, who is now 69, says he decided to sell the manuscript for the song, which he wrote in Cold Springs, New York and Philadelphia, on a whim.

He has previously admitted that the beginning of the eight-minute tune is about the death of singer Buddy Holly, who died in a plane crash with Ritchie Valens and JP Richardson in 1959.

However, he has been elusive about the meaning behind most of the lyrics, which has heightened interest and led to countless interpretations.

